I have a website with a main landing page, a client portal, and a user portal. Add a persistent nav bar to both portal pages that lets users navigate back to the main landing page.

Requirements:
- Fixed nav bar at top of both portals, height 64px
- Linkwright logo (SVG L-bracket mark) top-left, clicking it goes to index.html or /
- "Back to main site" text link on the right side of the nav
- Style: background #F4F1EC at 95% opacity, backdrop blur, 0.5px bottom border rgba(26,24,20,0.1)
- Font: DM Sans, charcoal #1A1814
- Add padding-top: 64px to portal body so content clears the nav
- Mobile friendly

Logo SVG to use:
<svg width="36" height="36" viewBox="0 0 36 36" fill="none"><rect x="8" y="6" width="2.2" height="22" fill="#1A1814"/><rect x="8" y="26" width="13" height="2.2" fill="#1A1814"/><rect x="17.5" y="13" width="1.6" height="8" fill="#1A1814"/><rect x="17.5" y="19.4" width="5.5" height="1.6" fill="#1A1814"/></svg>

